# Local overrides for scripts/ci-local.sh (and any docker-compose-based command).
#
# When this file is copied to `.env.ci-local` at the repo root, ci-local.sh
# sources it *before* running `docker compose up -d`. It's gitignored (matches
# .env.*) so your real internal-registry URLs never land in git.
#
# Use case: corporate networks that block docker.io. Point POSTGRES_IMAGE /
# REDIS_IMAGE at an internal Harbor mirror — or any registry that proxies
# Docker Hub — whose whitelist includes the tag you need.
#
# Cross-platform note (Apple Silicon):
#   Some mirrors only whitelist the x86_64 manifest for -alpine tags, so
#   `redis:7-alpine` fails to pull on arm64 even though it works fine on Linux
#   runners. Two workarounds that have worked locally:
#     1. Swap to the plain (Debian) tag that has a multi-arch manifest:
#          REDIS_IMAGE=<mirror>/redis:7
#     2. Pin the arm64 image by digest (same pattern the license-infra
#        reference project uses):
#          REDIS_IMAGE=<mirror>/redis@sha256:<arm64-digest>
#
# Copy to .env.ci-local and fill in your real mirror host:
#   cp .env.ci-local.example .env.ci-local
#
# Then edit POSTGRES_IMAGE / REDIS_IMAGE below to match your whitelist.

# POSTGRES_IMAGE=harbor-docker.payoharbor.com/whitelist/postgres:16-alpine
# REDIS_IMAGE=harbor-docker.payoharbor.com/whitelist/redis:7

# The docker/*.Dockerfile images that build the 3 backends + 3 frontends also
# need a mirrored base. Setting NODE_IMAGE here threads through to every
# service's `build.args.NODE_IMAGE` in docker-compose.yml.
# NODE_IMAGE=harbor-docker.payoharbor.com/whitelist/node:22-alpine

# Optional: if you want ci:local to skip the Playwright install on repeat runs.
# PLAYWRIGHT_SKIP_BROWSER_DOWNLOAD=1
